March 21 at 9:39 AM ¬∑

Please Spread the Word: Schools Can Donate Medical Supplies

Yesterday MCSD donated medical supplies to our local hospital. We could not think of someone in need or medical staff without or reusing a mask when there we some on a shelf in our empty buildings. While we could not give much, or deplete our supply, we could spare some to help. If a small district like ours can do it, any district can.

There are over 13,000 school districts and CTCs in the United States. Please spread the word for schools to consider helping by donating supplies (masks, gloves, swabs, etc.) to local hospitals and/or EMS if they haven‚Äôt already. I am sure it will be appreciated. Stay healthy!!!

post_text: Featuring some of our Middle School students!
shared_text:
The Mon Valley Independent
May 14, 2019 at 12:11 AM ¬∑

Running is group effort for Monessen contingent

By Kaylie Moore
kmoore@yourmvi.com
For the second consecutive year, Monessen Middle School teacher Stephanie Kirkpatrick has combined her two passions to create memories with her students.
An English language arts teacher and the district‚Äôs student council sponsor, Kirkpatrick recently participated in the Pittsburgh Marathon 5K with a group of 46 students and parents.
‚ÄúEvery week after school, with the help of (teacher) Jen Cicchini, the students would stay after for an hour to train for the race,‚Äù Kirkpatrick said.
Last year, Kirkpatrick took 25 sixth-graders and their parents to run the 5K (3.1 miles), which is part of the Pittsburgh Marathon weekend. In addition to the 5k, events include a 1-mile run for kids, toddler trot, pet walk, half marathon (13.1 miles) and full marathon (26.2 miles).

See more on our website at https://e.monvalleyindependent.com.

post_text: As we get ready to start Teacher Appreciation week, I would like to thank 2 very special teachers. This weekend, Nicole Turkovich Johnson sponsored and set up a hugely successful Father Daughter Dance. All of the beautiful, happy pictures were so wonderful to see on FB! On Saturday, Mrs. Kirkpatrick took a group of students and parents to the Pittsburgh 5K run. This is just two examples of the hard working, dedicated, caring and compassionate teachers we have in our district! Thank you ladies for all you do for our children. And thank you to all of the teachers in our district for everything you do! We appreciate you more than you know!
